The '''Angolan National Democratic Party''' (''Partido Nacional Democrático Angolano'') is a [[political party]] in [[Angola]]. The chairman of the party is Geraldo Pereira João da Silva and the general secretary is Pedro João António. In the [[Elections in Angola|1992 presidential election]] the party supported the independent candidate Daniel Julio Chipenda.

In 1997 the party passed through some internal strife, at the time of its first national conference.

