The '''IPCT''' (International Professional Cycling Teams) was created in 2006 by 17 of the 18 [[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]] [[UCI ProTour|ProTour]] teams. It is a [[Groupement d'Intérêt Economique|GIE]] whose aim is to represent the 17 teams in all matters of common interests. The [[Headquarters|HQ]], based in [[Brussels]] is run by [[Gerrit Middag]], who previously worked for the UCI.

The 17 current (2008 season) members are : {{ct|A2R|2008}}, {{ct|AST|2008}}, {{ct|GCE|2008}}, {{ct|BTL|2008}}, {{ct|COF|2008}}, {{ct|C.A|2008}}, {{ct|EUS|2008}}, {{ct|GST|2008}}, {{ct|LAM|2008}}, {{ct|LIQ|2008}}, {{ct|SIL|2008}}, {{ct|QST|2008}}, {{ct|RAB|2008}}, {{ct|SDV|2008a}}, {{ct|CSC|2008a}}, {{ct|THR|2008a}}, {{ct|MRM|2008}}.

