The '''Livoberezhna line''' ({{lang-uk|Лівобережна лінія}}) is the second line of the [[Kiev Light Rail]] system, which serves [[Kiev]]'s [[Troieschyna]] neighborhood on the city's left bank. It was originally opened on May 26, 2000, rebuilt from 2010-2012, and reopened again on October 25, 2012.<ref name=uni>{{cite web|title=The tram will run towards Troieschyna on Thursday|url=http://www.unian.ua/society/706033-na-troeschinu-u-chetver-zapustyat-tramvay-tijden-katatimut-bezplatno.html|work=[[Ukrainian Independent Information Agency|UNIAN]]|accessdate=29 April 2014|language=Ukrainian|date=19 October 2012}}</ref>
At one point, the [[Kiev City State Administration|Kiev City Administration]] proposed extending the [[Kiev Metro]] system to Troieschyna by creating the [[Livoberezhna line (Kiev Metro)|Livoberezhna line]], although this proposal was scrapped in 2014 in favor of keeping the light rail system.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kiev authorities have decided not to build a metro to Troieschyna|url=http://www.pravda.com.ua/rus/news/2014/04/7/7021632/|work=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]]|accessdate=29 April 2014|date=7 April 2014|language=Russian}}</ref>
==List of stations== The Livoberezhna line consists of a total of seven full stations, and seven tram stops, which are served by the Kiev Light Rail's fourth and fifth routes. It contains a total of {{Convert|13.2|km|mi|lk=on}} of track. The line is serviced by the [[Darnytsia]] tram depot. Listed from north to south, the stations are:
* [[Myloslavska (Kiev Light Rail)|Myloslavska]] * [[Maryny Tsvetaievoi (Kiev Light Rail)|Maryny Tsvetaievoi]] * [[Oleksandra Saburova (Kiev Light Rail)|Oleksandra Saburova]] (2000–2008, Saburova) * [[Teodora Draizera (Kiev Light Rail)|Teodora Draizera]] (2000–2008, Draizera) * [[Kashtanova (Kiev Light Rail)|Kashtanova]] * [[Henerala Vatutina (Kiev Light Rail)|Henerala Vatutina]] (2000–2008, Vatutina) * [[Troieschyna-2 (Kiev Light Rail)|Troieschyna-2]] (opened on October 25, 2012)
