'''''Men Don't Cry''''' ({{lang-bs|'''Muškarci ne plaču'''}}) is a 2017 Bosnian [[drama film]] directed by [[Alen Drljević]].<ref name="HWR">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/men-don-t-cry-muskarci-koji-ne-placu-1020276 |title='Men Don’t Cry' ('Muskarci koji ne placu'): Film Review Karlovy Vary 2017 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=12 July 2017 |accessdate=18 August 2017}}</ref> It was selected as the Bosnian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[90th Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref name="Bosnia">{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/film-tv/film-muskarci-ne-placu-je-bh-kandidat-za-nagradu-oscar/170817061 |title=Film "Muškarci ne plaču" je bh. kandidat za nagradu Oscar |work=Klix |date=17 August 2017 |accessdate=18 August 2017}}</ref><ref name="SD">{{cite web|url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/bosnia-picks-men-dont-cry-for-foreign-language-oscar-race/5120956.article |title=Bosnia picks 'Men Don't Cry' for foreign language Oscar race |work=ScreenDaily |first=Tom |last=Grater |date=18 August 2017 |accessdate=18 August 2017}}</ref> The film won the 2017 [[Special Jury Prize (Karlovy Vary IFF)|Special Jury Prize]] at the [[52nd Karlovy Vary International Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.kviff.com/en/history/2017 2017 awards at the official site]</ref>
==Plot== A group of disparate, middle-aged [[Yugoslav Wars|Yugoslav War]] veterans talk in an extended group-therapy session.<ref name="HWR" />
