'''Movement for Citizens' Commitment and Awakening''' ({{Lang-fr|Mouvement pour l'engagement et le réveil des citoyens}}, abbreviated '''MERCI''') is a [[political party]] in [[Benin]] led by [[Séverin Adjovi]].

In the 1999 parliamentary elections, MERCI elected two MPs: Amadou Assouma and Sacca Moussèdikou Fikara.

