The '''Takua people''' are an ethnic group of Vietnam.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Carrier|first1=Joseph|title=Surviving War, Surviving Peace|date=2007|page=15|url=http://www.lib.uci.edu/about/publications/images/checklist_survivingwar.pdf|accessdate=20 June 2014}}</ref> They live in the heavily forested mountainous regions of [[Quảng Nam Province|Quảng Nam]] and [[Quảng Ngãi Province|Quảng Ngãi]] provinces in Central Vietnam.

